Description: Fragment of handle at neck join of Pamphylian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine orange-buff; small mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 58. Name Nikon. As. C. Brixhe, Timbres amphoriques de Pamphylie (Paris, 2012) no. 323
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0075)
